Emil Sinclair is Sinclair is the protagonist and the narrator ofDemian.The book is a chronicle of his intellectual development from the time he was ten until his late teens. An older Sinclair (who is at least middle aged) tells the stories of his youth that played a key role in his personal growth.Demianrecounts the story of Sinclair's interactions with Demian and a host of other characters who are instrumental in his intellectual transformation. This intellectual transformation is one that changes Demian from a religious boy who follows others' commands to a man who seeks to be aware of, and fulfill the deepest desires of, his soul.